The '''National Football League Management Council''' is a [[non-profit organization|non-profit]] association of clubs in the [[National Football League]] (NFL) that represents its members in negotiations related to the  [[Collective bargaining|Collective Bargaining Agreement]] with the [[National Football League Players Association|NFL Players Association]].<ref name="ariz">{{cite web|url=http://news.justia.com/cases/featured/arizona/azdce/2:2008cv01541/399304/|title=''Arizona Cardinals Football Club, Inc. et al v. Bryant et al''|date=2008-08-20|publisher=U.S. District Court for the District of Arizona|accessdate=2009-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nflplayers.com/images/fck/NFL%20COLLECTIVE%20BARGAINING%20AGREEMENT%202006%20-%202012.pdf|title=NFL Collective Bargaining Agreement 2006-2012|date=2006-03-06|publisher=NFL Players Association|accessdate=2009-03-13}}</ref>  It is based in [[New York City]] and its chairman is the NFL Executive Vice President of Labor Relations, Harold Henderson.<ref name="ariz"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.globeinvestor.com/servlet/ArticleNews/story/PRNEWS/20060204/NYSA003|title=NFL's Harold Henderson Honored During Super Bowl Festivities|date=2006-02-04|work=News from PR newswire|location=Toronto, Ont.|publisher=The Globe and Mail|accessdate=2009-03-13}}</ref>

